{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"ida9e677f7-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s2860"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2860"},"text":"§ 2860.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Availability of appropriations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Funds appropriated to a military department or to the Secretary of Defense for a fiscal year for military construction or military family housing purposes may remain available for obligation beyond such fiscal year to the extent provided in appropriation Acts.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"ida9e677f8-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"(Added ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/214/s2/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–214, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-07-12"},"text":"July 12, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/167"},"text":"96 Stat. 167","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/167/tVIII/s812/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–167, title VIII, § 812(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/991"},"text":"99 Stat. 991","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/173/s121/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–173, § 121(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-12-10"},"text":"Dec. 10, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/1029"},"text":"99 Stat. 1029","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/661/dA/tXIII/s1343/a/21/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–661, div. A, title XIII, § 1343(a)(21)(A)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-11-14"},"text":"Nov. 14, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/3994"},"text":"100 Stat. 3994","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"ida9e677f9-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"ida9e677fa-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"ida9e677fb-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/661"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–661","children":[],"tail":" substituted “to the Secretary of Defense” for “defense agency”, inserted “for obligation” after “remains available”, and struck out “the” before “appropriation Acts”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1985—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/173"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–173","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Availability of appropriations” for “Availability of appropriations for five years” as section catchline, and amended text generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “Subject to the provisions of appropriation Acts, any funds appropriated to a military department or defense agency for the construction of military projects may be obligated for a military construction project or contract, or for any portion of such a project or contract, at any time before the end of the fourth fiscal year after the fiscal year for which funds for such project were appropriated if the funds obligated for such project (1) are obligated from funds available for military construction projects, and (2) do not exceed the amount appropriated for such project, plus any amount by which the cost of such project is increased pursuant to law.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/167"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–167","children":[],"tail":" struck out subsection designation “(a)” and “and except as otherwise provided under subsection (b)” after “provisions of appropriation Acts”, and struck out subsec. (b) which provided: “Should a requirement develop to obligate funds for a military construction project after the end of the fourth fiscal year after the fiscal year for which such funds were appropriated, such obligation may be made after the end of the 21-day period beginning on the date on which the appropriate committees of Congress receive notification of the need for such obligation and the reasons therefor.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"ida9e677fc-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"ida9e677fd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1985 Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/173/s121/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–173, § 121(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-12-10"},"text":"Dec. 10, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/1029"},"text":"99 Stat. 1029","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/99/173/s121/c"},"text":"“The amendment made by subsection (b) [amending this section] shall apply to funds appropriated after the date of the enactment of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/103"},"text":"Public Law 99–103","children":[],"tail":" ["},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 1985","children":[],"tail":"].”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/167/tVIII/s812/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–167, title VIII, § 812(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-12-03"},"text":"Dec. 3, 1985","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/99/991"},"text":"99 Stat. 991","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/99/167/tVIII/s812/b"},"text":"“The amendments made by subsection (a) [amending this section] shall apply to funds appropriated after ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1985-09-30"},"text":"September 30, 1985","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"ida9e677fe-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"For effective date and applicability of section, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/214/s12/a"},"text":"section 12(a) of Pub. L. 97–214","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s2801"},"text":"section 2801 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"ida9e677ff-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Availability of Appropriations for Five Years","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/114/tI/s117"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–114, title I, § 117","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2005-11-30"},"text":"Nov. 30, 2005","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"re